doctype html
html
  head
    link(href='//maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootswatch/3.3.5/darkly/bootstrap.min.css', rel='stylesheet')
    meta(name="viewport",content="width=device-width,height=device-height,white-space:normal, initial-scale=1.0")
  body
    div.navbar.navbar-default
      div(style='text-align:center; color: #FFFFFF')
        h1 iErgo
    div.container
      div.jumbotron(style='text-align:center')
        h1(style='text-align:center')#header
          | Rodgers Muscle Fatigue Model
        .panel-group
          .panel.panel-info
            h2(style='text-align:center')
              | Purpose:
            panel-body
              h4 
                | To provide a method of evaluating the physiological demands of a task against published criteria of acceptable levels of oxygen consumption for whole body or upper bodywork.
        div.panel.panel-info
            h2(style='text-align:center')
              | Developed by:
            panel-body
            h4 
              | Suzanne Rodgers
        div.panel.panel-info
            h2(style='text-align:center')
              | Developed When:
            panel-body
            h4 
              | 1978-1992
        div.panel.panel-info
            h2(style='text-align:center')
              | Musculoskeletal Disorder Risk Factors Considered:
            panel-body
            h4 
              | Fatigue
        div.panel.panel-info
            h2(style='text-align:center')
              | Body Regions Considered:
            panel-body
            h4 
              | Neck, shoulder, hand, wrist, arm, back, legs, elbow, and knee
        div.panel.panel-info
            h2(style='text-align:center')
              | Type of Jobs Appropriate For:
            panel-body
            h4 
              | Jobs that require high frequency and duration, and have awkward postures
        div.panel.panel-info
            h2(style='text-align:center')
              | Type of Jobs Not Appropriate For:
            panel-body
            h4 
              | Non-fatiguing job analysis, and seated jobs
        div.panel.panel-info
            h2(style='text-align:center')
              | Limitations:
            panel-body
            h4 
              | Any task evaluated is limited to 30 seconds of continuous effort and 15 minutes of effort frequency. After this point, the job is considered very high priority. No numerical value is assigned after this point.
        div.panel.panel-info
            h2(style='text-align:center')
              | Who is the Tool Design For:
            panel-body
            h4 
              | Professional users
        div.panel.panel-info
            h2(style='text-align:center')
              | Minimal Amount of Training:
            panel-body
            h4 
              | 8 hours
        div.panel.panel-info
            h2(style='text-align:center')
              | Studies That Provide Evidence of Validation of the Tool:
            panel-body
            h4 
              | None currently found in literature
        div.panel.panel-info
            h2(style='text-align:center')
              | Electronic Version:
            panel-body
            h4 
              a(href='http://personal.health.usf.edu/tbernard/HollowHills/Rodgers_MFA_M20.pdf') Muscle Fatigue Analysis.pdf
        div.panel.panel-info
            h2(style='text-align:center')
              | Reference of Peer-Reviewed Publication:
            panel-body
            h4 
              | Suzanne H. Rodgers, A functional job evaluation technique, in Ergonomics, edited by J.S.Moore and A. Garg 
              br
              | Occupational Medicine: State of the Art Reviews. 7(4):679-711, 1992.
              br
              br
              | Suzanne H. Rodgers, Job evaluation in worker fitness determination
              br
              | Occupational Medicine: State of the
              | Art Reviews. 3(2):219-239, 1988.
        div.panel.panel-info
            h2(style='text-align:center')
              | Industries and Jobs Where Tool Has Been Applied:
            panel-body
            h4 
              | General manufacturing, construction, and healthcare
        div.panel.panel-info
            h2(style='text-align:center')
              | Is Tool Copyrighted:
            panel-body
            h4 
              | No
        div.panel.panel-info
            h2(style='text-align:center')
              | Instructional or Supplemental Information:
            panel-body
            h4 
              a(href='http://personal.health.usf.edu/tbernard/HollowHills/Rodgers_MFA_M20.pdf') Muscle Fatigue Analysis.pdf
        div.panel.panel-info
            h2(style='text-align:center')
              | Equipment Needed to Use Tool:
            panel-body
            h4 
              | None
        div.panel.panel-info
            h2(style='text-align:center')
              | Time Required Analyzing Typical Job:
            panel-body
            h4 
              | 1-2 hours
        br
        p(style='text-align:left')
          a.btn-lg.btn-danger(href="/tool_definitions") Back

